  "notes": "Classical Sanskrit (Pāṇinian standard, c. 4th c. BCE onward). Five-point place-of-articulation system: velar, palatal, retroflex, dental, labial. Four-way laryngeal contrast (plain/aspirated × voiced/voiceless). No short /e/ or /o/ (only long). ⟨व⟩ = [ʋ] labiodental approximant. Sandhi rules are extensive but modeled at the allophone level here.",
